c:20770.name: US & EU Oxford COVID-19 Government Response Stringency Index
c:20770.description:
The Oxford COVID-19 Government Response Stringency Index is gathered by the University of Oxford, composed of 9 subindices:

1. School closing
2. Workplace closing
3. Cancel public events
4. Restrictions on gatherings
5. Close public transport
6. Stay at home requirements
7. Restrictions on internal movement
8. International travel controls
9. Public info campaigns

The reading = The average score of 9 subindices * 100%
The higher the reading is, the more strict the government measures are. A decrease in stringency suggests certain degree of loosening of restrictions.

c:22281.name: Global Flight Tracking
c:22281.description:
The number of daily flights is calculated by Flightradar counting the number of flights on the website.

Commercial flights: Commercial passenger flights + cargo flights + charter flights + some business jet flights.
Total flights: Commercial flights above + rest of business jet flights + private flights + gliders + most helicopter flights + most ambulance flights + government flights + some military flights + drones

c:25738.name: Google Community Mobility Reports: Retail and Recreation
c:25738.description:
Google Community Mobility Reports are created with aggregated, anonymized sets of data from users who have turned on the Location History setting.

The data shows how visitors to (or time spent in) categorized places change compared to our baseline days. A baseline day represents a normal value for that day of the week. The baseline day is the median value from the 5‑week period Jan 3 – Feb 6, 2020.

The reports chart movement trends over time by geography, across different categories of places such as retail and recreation, groceries and pharmacies, parks, transit stations, workplaces, and residential.
